<h3 style="font-family:Arial; font-size:20pt; color:#a51681">
Autumn Statement: Reinforcing sustainable growth or reinforcing the messaging?</h3>
<hr />
</td></tr>
<tr><td width="50%" valign="top">
<p align="left" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">
<i>With this being the Chancellor’s last Autumn Statement before the General Election, he will need to balance 

the country’s needs with political realities.</i> 
<br /><br />
AECOM and <i>Construction News</i> are pleased to host a panel of esteemed industry and government experts who 

will discuss and debate whether the Chancellor has taken the right measures to address the UK’s most pressing 

needs while also ensuring the property and construction industry is positioned for sustainable growth.
</p>
<p align="left" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt;">
During the session, we will discuss:
</p>
<ul align="left" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; padding-left:12px">
<li>Maintaining London’s global competitiveness</li> 
<li>Bridging the north-south divide</li>
<li>Investment in hard and social infrastructure</li>
<li>Addressing the industry’s skills shortage</li>
<li>London’s housing demand</li>
</ul>


</td><td width="50%" valign="top">



<p align="left" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">
<b>Panel:</b>
<ul align="left" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; padding-left:12px">
<li><b>David Leam</b>, Executive Director – Policy, London First</li>
<li><b>Denise Chevin</b> (Chair), Acting Editor, Construction News 
<li><b>Rt. Hon. David Lammy MP</b>
<li><b>Martin Rowark</b>, Director of Commercial, Transport for London
<li><b>John Hicks</b>, Head of Government & Public, AECOM
</ul>

</p><p align="left" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt;">

